Class DatabaseConditionFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • hr.fer.zemris.java.tecaj.hw5.db.conditions.DatabaseConditionFactory

  • public class DatabaseConditionFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    Factory class for producing DatabaseCondition and DatabaseToken objects. Also contains all conditions used for lexical analysis conditions.

    1.0
    Author:

      • produce

        public static DatabaseCondition produce(java.lang.String conditions)
        Produces a DatabaseCondition from the given string. String unit should be made from a keyword, followed by an operator found in DatabaseOperatorFactory followed by a literal value denoted by " signs. String units can be aggregated by the AND keyword. Throws IllegalArgumentException if given null as argument.
        Parameters:
        conditions - string containing the conditions
        Returns:
        returns the produced condition
